title: High school girls volleyball: Area teams primed for playoffs, ready to hit road to state finals
text:
Sectional: Guerin 
Sectional seed: No. 2 
First match: 6 p.m. Oct. 27 vs. No. 9 Collins Academy/No. 10 Our Lady of Tepeyac 
Outlook: The No. 2 seed in a dub-divided sectional, the Trojans have been tested all season against larger schools in tournaments including wins at both the St. Viator and Manteno invites. A 25-22, 25-18 win against Latin on Oct. 20 moved TC's record to 30-4 overall. Dani Van Laten had 16 assists, Ava Venema recorded six kills and Tracy Westra had eight digs and three kills in the win. 
If the Trojans win the regional opener they would advance to the regional final on Oct. 29 against either Walther Christian or St. Joseph. TC topped Walther in two games on Sept. 24 and closed the regular season against the Broncos on Oct. 22. 
West Chicago
